James Paul Harris, 30, pleaded no contest in December to involuntary manslaughter in the 2011 garroting death of 49-year-old James Gerety . 
  Harris originally was charged with first-degree murder in the beheading death of the victim . 
  On Monday, a judge sentenced Harris to four years and two months in prison . 
  The victim's brother said the justice system is 'a joke'